    <h1 class="title topictitle1" id="ariaid-title1">VMD
        Server</h1>

    
    <div class="body"><p class="shortdesc">The <em class="ph i">Video Motion Detection (VMD)</em> helps with the automatic analysis of IR
        camera video streams. </p>

        <p class="p"><em class="ph i">Video Motion Detection</em> is an electro-optical based solution to complete radar
            based target detection and tracking. It acts as a sensor and displays <em class="ph i">VMD Alarms</em>
            on the cartography. The <em class="ph i">VMD Server</em> is located in the <em class="ph i">Ground Shelter</em>.</p>

        <p class="p">The <em class="ph i">VMD Server</em> analyzes video contents and sends the result of this process to its
            clients. For this, it emits its own CCTV multicast stream on the network, like a
            standard CCTV camera. The workstation (client) is configured to display this camera
            stream.</p>

        <p class="p"><em class="ph i">VMD</em> is able to detect an intrusion in a defined area. It processes an
            Analog/Digital data input from an IR camera to detect movement by displaying a marker in
            an alarm zone when a moving object is detected. Each time an intrusion is detected
            inside an alarm zone, an alarm is sent from the <em class="ph i">VMD Server</em> to the <em class="ph i">MS
                Application Server ‘Alarm Manager’</em>. The alarms are furthermore displayed at the
                <em class="ph i">MS Client</em>.</p>

    </div>

